@sandakersmann 

> @morcos When your transaction is stuck in limbo it is better that it is only stuck for 3 days and not 14.

When a transaction is stuck in limbo, it is usually due to too low fees. In that case, it will have been evicted from the mempool already, and the timeout doesn't affect it at all. The reason the timeout exists is for robustness against unexpected events such as unk
